content.description: Crux is high. Hugs right of a small roof.
content.location: Right of the hanging Gardens of Denny and left of Liquid Amber

content.description: Super-fun, steep roof chug on climbers-right side of the crag. Find the stacked tiers. Start up on the chossy ledge, from some boulders, and get shoulder cranking straight away. Unlock each roof--one, two, three, four--in a slightly different way, then victory finish up incut iron patina edges. Kind of an exemplar of the overhanging Cumberland tier climbing--not a Moon Board, more of an upside-down staircase. Excellent rock for the most part.
content.location: Scramble up on shaled ledge to flat alcove with a few boulders. Start left of side of corner crack, or straight up off boulders. Blast up and right. Climbers-right side of crag--the steeper one.

content.description: 1st route to the left of the large roof feature. Pull a low roof followed by continuous steep and technical climbing. Really solid rock after the 1st bolt. This route is worth getting on.
content.location: Around the corner from the Buffet Wall, past the waterfall. 3rd route you pass coming from that direction. Left of the large roof.

content.description: Left-most route on wall. Stick clip. Start in a blocky alcove set between trees. Crank big, fun moves up steep grey rock, on large holds. Moving into orange rock, swing right a move or two on a rail, then do some more big pulls on jugs up a bluntish prow. Pass an awesome pocket, then gain a ledge. Ladder on to finish up an orange face left of a corner.
content.location: Climbers-left side of wall. Left-most route as of 11/8/21. Shady, block alcove between some trees. Steep grey rock start, then more very orange rock up higher.

content.description: Currently 7 routes with a good variety of difficulty from 5.10 to 5.12. This wall also has a large variety of features.
